                  <span class="text-sm sm:text-base font-medium text-white">
                    How does FormGuard actually monitor my WordPress forms?
                  </span>
                  <span class="faq-icon ml-4 flex-shrink-0 text-gray-400 transition-transform duration-300">
                    <!-- Heroicon Chevron Down -->
                    <svg class="w-5 h-5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
                      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25 12 15.75 4.5 8.25" />
                    </svg>
                  </span>
                </button>
                <div class="faq-answer px-5 pb-4 pt-0 hidden">
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed pt-1">
                    We start by identifying the forms that are critical to your business—contact, quote, booking, demos, lead magnets, and more. FormGuard then runs scheduled test submissions that mimic real users, checking not only that the form can be submitted, but also that confirmation emails and notifications are delivered correctly. If a problem is detected at any point in that chain, we trigger an instant alert with detailed context so your team can fix the issue quickly.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
              <div class="faq-item border border-gray-800/80 bg-gray-950/80 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
                <button class="faq-question w-full flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 text-left hover:bg-gray-900/80 cursor-pointer transition-all duration-300">
                  <span class="text-sm sm:text-base font-medium text-white">
                    Will FormGuard slow down my site or interfere with real visitors?
                  </span>
                  <span class="faq-icon ml-4 flex-shrink-0 text-gray-400 transition-transform duration-300">
                    <svg class="w-5 h-5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
                      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25 12 15.75 4.5 8.25" />
                    </svg>
                  </span>
                </button>
                <div class="faq-answer px-5 pb-4 pt-0 hidden">
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed pt-1">
                    No. FormGuard runs lightweight, scheduled tests that behave like a single user filling out the form. These checks are intentionally low-frequency and optimized to avoid impacting performance or analytics. We do not inject heavy scripts or permanently add bloat to your pages. Most clients never see any measurable change in site speed or server load—instead, they simply gain visibility and protection.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
              <div class="faq-item border border-gray-800/80 bg-gray-950/80 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
                <button class="faq-question w-full flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 text-left hover:bg-gray-900/80 cursor-pointer transition-all duration-300">
                  <span class="text-sm sm:text-base font-medium text-white">
                    Do I need to install a plugin or manage another dashboard?
                  </span>
                  <span class="faq-icon ml-4 flex-shrink-0 text-gray-400 transition-transform duration-300">
                    <svg class="w-5 h-5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
                      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25 12 15.75 4.5 8.25" />
                    </svg>
                  </span>
                </button>
                <div class="faq-answer px-5 pb-4 pt-0 hidden">
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed pt-1">
                    FormGuard is intentionally designed as a managed service, not another SaaS tool you have to babysit. We handle the technical setup and monitoring configuration for you. In most cases, we integrate using existing access you already provide to manage your site. You receive alerts, health summaries, and clear reports via email or your preferred communication channels—no extra login or dashboard required.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
              <div class="faq-item border border-gray-800/80 bg-gray-950/80 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
                <button class="faq-question w-full flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 text-left hover:bg-gray-900/80 cursor-pointer transition-all duration-300">
                  <span class="text-sm sm:text-base font-medium text-white">
                    What kinds of issues can FormGuard detect beyond simple form errors?
                  </span>
                  <span class="faq-icon ml-4 flex-shrink-0 text-gray-400 transition-transform duration-300">
                    <svg class="w-5 h-5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
                      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25 12 15.75 4.5 8.25" />
                    </svg>
                  </span>
                </button>
                <div class="faq-answer px-5 pb-4 pt-0 hidden">
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed pt-1">
                    Beyond obvious “form won’t submit” errors, FormGuard commonly detects broken SMTP configurations, changes in spam filters, plugin conflicts, JavaScript errors introduced by new tracking scripts, misconfigured reCAPTCHA, and hosting-level issues that block outbound mail. Because we follow the entire journey of a submission, we can flag problems that normal uptime monitoring or basic QA would never catch.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
              <div class="faq-item border border-gray-800/80 bg-gray-950/80 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
